{"title_page": "What Makes You Beautiful", "text_new": "{{Good article}}\n{{EngvarB|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = What Makes You Beautiful\n| cover      = <noinclude>What Makes You Beautiful Album Cover.jpg</noinclude>\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[One Direction]]\n| album      = [[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]\n| B-side     = Na Na Na\n| released   = {{Start date|2011|09|11|df=y}}\n| format     = \n*[[CD single]]\n*[[Music download|digital download]]\n| recorded   = July 2011\n| studio     = \n*Malibu, California\n*Kinglet & [[Cosmos Studios]], [[Stockholm]], Sweden\n| genre      = [[Power pop]]<ref name=Powerpop>{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/up-all-night-20120328 |title=One Direction \u2013 Up All Night |work=Rolling Stone |publisher=Jann Wenner |first=Jody |last=Rosen |date=28 March 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref>\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=18}}\n| label      = \n*[[Syco Music|Syco]]\n*[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| writer     = \n*[[Savan Kotecha]]\n*[[Rami Yacoub]]\n*[[Carl Falk]]\n| producer   = \n*Gonzalo Palafox\n*Carl Falk\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Gotta Be You (One Direction song)|Gotta Be You]]\n| next_year  = 2011\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|QJO3ROT-A4E|\"What Makes You Beautiful\"}}\n }}\n}}\n\"'''What Makes You Beautiful'''\" is a song by English-Irish [[boy band]] [[One Direction]]. It served as their debut single and lead single from their debut studio album, ''[[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]'' (2011). Written by [[Savan Kotecha]] and producer [[Rami Yacoub]], the song was released by [[Syco Records]] on 11 September 2011. The uptempo [[power pop]]<ref name=Powerpop/> track features a prominent guitar-based chorus and [[riff]]. The [[middle eight]] consists of a \"na na na\" [[hook (music)|hook]] while the opening guitar riff interpolates [[The McCoys]]'s 1965 single \"[[Hang on Sloopy]]\".\n'What makes you beautiful\" was written for a very special person called ADA\n\n\"What Makes You Beautiful\" was a commercial success, reaching number one in several countries. It has been certified quadruple platinum in the US with sales of 4.8 million copies as of June 2016.<ref name=\"USsales2016\"/> The single peaked at number four on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and number one on the UK Singles Chart. The song won the [[2012 Brit Awards|2012]] [[Brit Award for British Single of the Year]] and was generally complimented by contemporary [[Music journalism|music critics]], who highlighted the appeal to the teenage audience and the pop sensibility. It debuted at number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]] after setting a [[Sony Music Entertainment]] pre-order record and selling 153,965 copies in its first week. The single also topped the [[Irish Singles Chart|Irish]] and [[Scottish Singles and Albums Charts|Scottish]] Singles Charts, and reached the top ten on the [[ARIA Charts|Australian]] and [[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand|New Zealand]] Singles Charts, Flemish [[Ultratop 50]], [[Canadian Hot 100]], and the [[Japan Hot 100]].\n\nThe accompanying [[music video]], directed by John Urbano, depicts One Direction spending time on a beach in [[Malibu, California]]. The music video was uploaded to YouTube on 19 August 2011 and has accumulated more than 1.1 billion views since it premiered.  The clip garnered the group three [[MTV Video Music Awards]] at the [[2012 MTV Video Music Awards|2012 ceremony]]. One Direction performed the song live on televised shows, at awards ceremonies, and on four of their major concert tours: [[Up All Night Tour]] (2011\u201312), [[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]] (2013), [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]] (2014) and [[On the Road Again Tour]] (2015). Harry Styles performed the song on his [[Harry Styles: Live on Tour|2017 solo tour]]. Artists including [[the Piano Guys]] have covered \"What Makes You Beautiful\".\n\n==Background and production==\n\"What Makes You Beautiful\" was written by [[Savan Kotecha]] and [[Carl Falk]], and was produced by Yacoub and Falk. Instrumentation was completed by Falk and Yacoub. Serban Ghenea handled the [[audio mixing (recorded music)|audio mixing]], Tom Coyne the [[audio mastering]], and John Hanes the [[mix engineer]]ing, for which Phil Seaford served as the assistant.<ref name=\"credits\"/> Discussing the song's conception, Kotecha said: {{cquote|I had the melody of the chorus in my song for about a year until I was in a hotel room in London with my wife and she was having a bad morning. She was like, \"Oh, I feel so ugly\" and I was like, \"No, you look beautiful. You don\u2019t know how beautiful you look.\" And I was like, \"Oh, crap! That\u2019s a good song! Hold on!\" And I wrote that down. I actually wrote the song for my wife, so I went to the studio and it took a process of a couple weeks to really tweak it, but the core of it was written within two days and then tweaked a few things here and there over a couple weeks, but I mean, I still have the text message from Harry [Styles]. When he heard the demo, I was in Miami on my way back to Sweden, and he sent me a text message saying, \"I think you got it. I think you got the one here.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Schillaci|first1=Sophie|title=Meet Savan Kotecha: The Man Behind One Direction's Rapid Rise to the Top (Q&A)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/one-direction-meet-man-rapid-418682|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=June 28, 2015|date=February 6, 2013}}</ref>}}\n\nAfter recording the song at [[Cosmos Studios]] and Kinglet Studios in [[Stockholm]], Sweden,<ref name=\"credits\"/> the band felt relieved to have a song that they were happy to release as their debut single. Band member [[Liam Payne]] called the song \"perfect\",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a330745/one-direction-debut-single-is-perfect.html |title=One Direction: 'Debut single is perfect' |first=Robert |last=Copsey |work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=Hearst Magazines UK |date=20 July 2011 |accessdate=4 January 2012}}</ref> and [[Harry Styles]] said, \"When we were recording in the studio we knew instantly that we wanted this track to be our first single.\"<ref name=\"premiere\"/> Styles spoke to [[MTV News]], \"I think for us we wanted to release something that wasn't cheesy but it was fun. It kind of represented us, I think it took us a while to find it but I think we found the right song.\" Payne added, \"We always wanted [the single] to be something that people didn't expect and then when we heard it, it wasn't what we expected either so it kind of fitted perfectly.\"<ref name=\"watch\">{{cite news |url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/one-direction/329291-one-direction-what-makes-you-beautiful-video |title=Watch One Direction's Video |publisher=[[MTV News]] ([[MTV (UK and Ireland)|MTV Networks]]) |date=20 August 2011 |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Release and promotion==\n\"What Makes You Beautiful\" premiered on [[BBC Radio 1]] on 10 August 2011,<ref name=\"premiere\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/s103/the-x-factor/news/a334259/one-direction-premiere-debut-single-what-makes-you-beautiful-listen.html |title=One Direction premiere debut single 'What Makes You Beautiful': Listen |first=Ryan |last=Love |work=Digital Spy|publisher=Hearst Magazines UK|date=10 August 2011 |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref> and was released by Syco Music in Europe, Australia and New Zealand via [[music download|digital download]] on 11 September 2011.<ref name=\"AUSiTunes\"/> A CD single was released in the United Kingdom on 12 September 2011,<ref name=\"UKCD\"/> and followed in Australia and Germany on 25 November 2011 and 2 December 2011, respectively.<ref name=\"AUSCD\"/><ref name=\"GERCD\"/> In North America, the single was released in Canada via digital download on 31 January 2012.<ref name=\"apple1\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/what-makes-you-beautiful-single/id474714569?s=143455&ign-mpt=uo%3D4 |title=What Makes You Beautiful \u2013 Single by One Direction |publisher=[[iTunes Store]] ([[Apple Inc.]]) |date=31 January 2012 |accessdate=31 January 2012}}</ref> It was issued 14 February 2012 in the United States<ref name=\"USrelease\">{{cite news|author=Amanda Hasaka |url=http://www.celebuzz.com/2012-02-14/one-directions-debut-single-what-makes-you-beautiful-now-available-on-itunes/ |title=One Direction's Debut Single 'What Makes You Beautiful' Now Available On iTunes! |work=[[Buzz Media|Celebuzz]]|publisher=[[Buzz Media]]|date=14 February 2012 |accessdate=15 February 2012}}</ref> and was sent by Columbia Records to US [[contemporary hit radio]] (CHR) playlists on 28 February 2012.<ref name=\"USCHR\"/>\n\nFor the North American release of ''Up All Night'' on 13 March 2012, [[Columbia Records]] executives used [[social media]] to shape its marketing campaign. Columbia Records co-chairman Steve Barnett and his team decided to reverse the usual pattern of releasing a single on radio. Instead the label mounted a four-month marketing campaign aimed at building a fan base through social media before a single was ever released or played on the radio. The social media campaign asked fans to sign petitions and to enter video competitions to win a concert in their town. The campaign was a success as One Direction's [[Facebook]] followers in the United States rose from 40,000 to 400,000. As a result, \"What Makes You Beautiful\" sold more than 131,000 copies in its first week, even though it had yet to be played on the radio. Radio programmers were flooded with calls from fans. [[Johnny Wright (music manager)|Johnny Wright]], who managed [[New Kids on the Block]], [[Backstreet Boys]] and [['N Sync]], said: \"Now they are calling the radio station, and the radio station is scratching its head, saying, \"We don't even have that record yet\". It's almost like the return of [[the Beatles]]. I call it hype, but it's positive hype because it's all real. It's not manufactured. No one paid these kids.\"<ref>{{cite news| author=James C. McKinley Jr| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/24/arts/music/one-direction-and-the-wanted-boy-bands-return.html?_r=2 |title=Boy Bands Are Back, Wholesome or Sexy|work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|date=23 March 2012|accessdate=30 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n{{Listen\n| filename    = What Makes You Beautiful.ogg\n| title       = \"What Makes You Beautiful\"\n| description = The song has a guitar-based chorus and riff\n| pos = left\n}}\n\"What Makes You Beautiful\" is a [[power pop]] song,<ref name=Powerpop/> with [[Synthpop|electropop]] influences.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/502856/one-direction-up-all-night-track-by-track-review |title=One Direction, 'Up All Night': Track-By-Track Review |first=Jason |last=Lipshutz |location=New York City|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=7 March 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> Running for 3 minutes and 23 seconds, the song is set in [[Time signature|common time]] with a [[tempo]] of 125 [[beats per minute]]. Written in the [[key (music)|key]] of [[E major]], it follows the [[chord progression]] E\u2013A\u2013B; vocal elements range from the note of B<sub>2</sub> to G{{music|sharp}}<sub>4</sub>.<ref name=\"MN\">{{cite web |url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0097775 |title=One Direction \u2013 What Makes You Beautiful Sheet Music |publisher=Musicnotes.com ([[EMI Music Publishing]]) |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> James C. McKinley Jr. of ''[[The New York Times]]'' compared its chord progression to \"[[La Bamba (song)|La Bamba]]\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/24/arts/music/one-direction-and-the-wanted-boy-bands-return.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all |title=Boy Bands Are Back, Wholesome or Sexy |first=James C. |last=McKinley |work=The New York Times |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |date=23 March 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> The opening guitar riff has been noted as similar to that of ''[[Grease (musical)|Grease]]'' single \"[[Summer Nights (Grease song)|Summer Nights]]\".<ref name=\"DS\"/> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" has a guitar-based chorus whose notes range from C to E; [[Digital Spy]]'s Robert Copsey likened it to a cross between [[Pink (singer)|Pink]]'s \"[[Raise Your Glass]]\" and [[McFly]]'s \"[[All About You/You've Got a Friend|All About You]]\".<ref name=\"DS\"/> It also contains [[cowbell (instrument)|cowbell]] instrumentation,<ref name=\"cowbell\">{{cite web|last=Houle |first=Zachary |url=https://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/155316-one-direction-up-all-night/ |title=One Direction: Up All Night|work=[[PopMatters]] |publisher=[[Buzz Media]]|date=16 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref> and the [[middle eight]] consists of an \"oh na na na\" hook.<ref name=\"NME\"/>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe song received generally positive reviews from [[Music journalism|music critics]]. Robert Copsey of [[Digital Spy]] gave \"What Makes You Beautiful\" four out of five stars, praising its catchy melody and summarising it as \"adorable, completely innocent and bound to cause a stir amongst your mates\".<ref name=\"DS\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a338401/one-direction-what-makes-you-beautiful-single-review.html |title=One Direction: 'What Makes You Beautiful' \u2013 Single review |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=Heart Magazines UK|first=Robert |last=Copsey |date=11 September 2011 |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> Zachary Houle of ''[[PopMatters]]'' called the song a \"nice get-up-and-go dance number.\"<ref name=\"cowbell\"/> Ailbhe Malone of ''[[NME]]'' commended the song's appeal to the teenage audience and its chord progression for being \"simple enough to be played on an acoustic guitar at a house party.\"<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite news |url=https://www.nme.com/blog/index.php?blog=148&title=one_direction_what_makes_you_beautiful_r&more=1&c=1&tb=1&pb=1 |title=One Direction, 'What Makes You Beautiful' \u2013 Review |work=NME |first=Ailbhe |last=Malone |date=8 October 2011 |publisher=[[IPC Media]] |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> ''[[Newsround]]'' called it \"fun, upbeat and incredibly catchy.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/14823863 |title=Review: One Direction \u2013 What Makes You Beautiful |work=[[Newsround]]|publisher=BBC|date=7 September 2011 |accessdate=31 March 2011}}</ref> [[AllMusic]]'s Matthew Chisling called it an \"effervescent and fresh tween love song\", and chose it as one of the best tracks on ''Up All Night''.<ref>{{cite news|author=Chisling, Matthew |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/up-all-night-r2324993/review |title=Up All Night \u2013 One Direction|work=[[AllMusic]] |publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]] |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref> Sophie Goddard from ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'' called the single \"ridiculously catchy\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cosmopolitan.co.uk/lifestyle/entertainment/cosmo-reviews-one-direction-album-up-all-night |title=Why there\u2019s only One Direction...Cosmo reviews their debut album |first=Sophie |last=Goddard |work=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]] |publisher=[[Hearst Corporation]] |date=25 November 2011 |accessdate=21 January 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111130052427/http://www.cosmopolitan.co.uk/lifestyle/entertainment/cosmo-reviews-one-direction-album-up-all-night |archive-date=30 November 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> ''[[The Student (newspaper)|Student]]''{{'s}} Jack Murray rated \"What Makes You Beautiful\" five out of five stars and called it \"not only the best pop single of the year so far, but potentially of any ''X Factor'' contestant ever\". Murray lauded the songwriting and light production.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.studentnewspaper.org/music/784-review-one-direction-what-makes-you-beautiful |title=Review: One Direction \u2013 What Makes You Beautiful |first=Jack |last=Murray |date=8 October 2011 |work=[[The Student (newspaper)|Student]] |publisher=[[The Student (newspaper)|The Student Newspaper]] Online|accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref> Tanner Stransky of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' awarded \"What Makes You Beautiful\" a B+ grade, calling the song \"shallow but crushworthy\", writing that the song shows that boy bands are not dying out.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20530309_20526759,00.html |title=Singles: Sept. 2, 2011 |date=8 September 2011 |work=Entertainment Weekly |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |first=Tanner |last=Stransky |accessdate=4 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nJason Lipshutz of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' characterised it as \"the real deal\", regarding the song as \"endlessly playable\" as [['N Sync]]'s \"[[Bye Bye Bye]]\". Lipshutz noted its \"cheeky electro-pop twist\".<ref name=\"Lipshutz\">{{cite news|author=Jason Lipshutz |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/502856/one-direction-up-all-night-track-by-track-review |title=One Direction, 'Up All Night': Track-By-Track Review |location=New York |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=7 March 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> Stephanie Abrahams of ''TIME'' assessed, \"The group takes cues from the boy bands of yesteryear with [[Bubblegum pop|bubblegum]] lyrics about young love \u2014 \u201cThe way you flip your hair gets me overwhelmed\u201d they croon in their breakout single \u2013 which any parent can get behind. That's a far cry from a typical [[Nicki Minaj]] verse.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Abrahams, Stephanie |url=http://entertainment.time.com/2012/04/06/behind-the-hype-can-one-direction-save-the-boy-band/#ixzz1rJSoTbQX |title=Can One Direction Save the Boy Band? |work=TIME |publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=6 April 2012 |accessdate= 27 April 2012}}</ref> ''[[The Observer]]'' editor [[Kitty Empire]] wrote in an assessment, \"With the exception of their persuasive No 1 single, \"What Makes You Beautiful\", their songs aren't wildly distinctive.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=[[Kitty Empire]] |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/jan/08/one-direction-x-factor-live |title=One Direction \u2013 review |date=7 January 2012 |work=The Observer |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |accessdate=8 April 2012|archiveurl=http://www.freezepage.com/1333939139CSPGVONNPC?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2012/jan/08/one-direction-x-factor-live |archivedate=9 April 2012 |location=London}}</ref> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" won the [[BRIT Award]] for [[2012 BRIT Awards|Best British Single]] at the 2012 [[Brit Awards]], which was held on 21 February 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/brit-awards-2012-british-single/ |title=One Direction Win Best British Single At BRIT Awards 2012 |work=Capital FM / [[Global Radio]]|date=21 February 2012|accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref> The song also won the [[Teen Choice Award]] for [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Music - Love Song|Choice Music: Love Song]] at the [[2012 Teen Choice Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Tina Hart |url=http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/swift-and-bieber-big-winners-at-teen-choice-awards/051089 |title=Swift and Bieber big winners at Teen Choice Awards |work=[[Music Week]] |publisher=Intent Media |date=23 July 2012 |accessdate=27 July 2012}}</ref> ''[[Newsround]]'' called the song \"fun, upbeat and incredibly catchy\" while commenting \"there's no way these boys won't be a hit\".<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/14823863</ref> Jim Hiscox of The ''[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]]'' named the song a \"confident, classic pop floorfiller\" and added that it is \"catchy without being cheesy\" and \"mature without trying to be cool\".<ref>https://www.dailystar.co.uk/music/review-one-direction-what-makes-18292603</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n[[File:One Direction Sydney 6.jpg|thumb|right|250px|One Direction performing \"What Makes You Beautiful\" at their [[Up All Night Tour]], 2012]]\n\"What Makes You Beautiful\" performed considerably well worldwide, but especially so in the British Isles, debuting at number 1 on the [[Irish Singles Chart]] on 15 September 2011; its B-side, \"Na Na Na\" also entered at number 27.<ref name=\"Ireland\"/> The single topped the chart for four consecutive weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/?i=1190&s=1111 |title=No Change Of Direction |work=Chart-track |publisher=GFK|date=7 October 2011 |accessdate=2012-03-31}}</ref> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" became the fourteenth best-selling single of 2011 on the Irish Singles Chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://irma.ie/best2011.htm#albums |title=IRMA - Irish Charts - Best of 2006 |publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association]] |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://irish-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=One+Direction |title=Discography One Direction |publisher=Irish-charts.com (Hung Medien) |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref> In the UK, \"What Makes You Beautiful\" received the highest ever number of [[pre-order]]s for a Sony Music Entertainment single.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a335956/one-directions-what-makes-you-beautiful-breaks-pre-order-sales-record.html |date=19 August 2011 |title=One Direction's 'What Makes You Beautiful' breaks pre-order sales record |first=Lewis |last=Corner |work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=Hearst Magazines UK}}</ref> It entered the [[UK Singles Chart]] at number 1 on 18 September 2011, shifting 153,965 copies that week\u2014the highest first-week UK sales for any song in 2011 at the time.<ref name=\"mw\">{{cite news |url=http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=22&storycode=1046622 |title=What Makes You Beautiful becomes fastest seller of the year |first=Alan |last=Jones |work=[[Music Week]] |publisher=Intent Media |date=19 September 2011 |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" also debuted at number 1 on the [[Scottish Singles and Albums Charts|Scottish Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"Scotchart\"/> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" was the 20th best-selling single of 2011, moving 540,000 copies,<ref name=\"endofyearUK\">{{cite news |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-top-20-biggest-selling-singles-of-2011-revealed/ |title=The Top 20 biggest selling singles of 2011 revealed! |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=2 January 2012 |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref> and was the 92nd best-selling single of the 21st century in the UK by May 2012.<ref>{{cite news|author=Lane, Dane |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-official-top-150-biggest-selling-singles-of-the-21st-century-revealed-1382/ |title=The official top 150 biggest selling singles of the 21st century revealed |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=15 May 2012 |accessdate=5 June 2012}}</ref> It has sold over 1,000,000 copies in the UK.<ref name=\"top 10 uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-s-official-top-10-biggest-selling-singles-revealed-__7226/|title=One Direction\u2019s Official Top 10 Biggest Selling Singles Revealed!|date=25 August 2015|first=Justin|last=Myers|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=25 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn Belgium, the song debuted at number 44 on both the [[Flanders|Flemish]] [[Ultratop 50]] and the [[Wallonia]]n [[Ultratip]]; it peaked at numbers 8 and 19, respectively.<ref name=\"Flanders\"/><ref name=\"Wallonia\"/> Accumulating twenty-two weeks on the [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|French Singles Chart]], it debuted at number 83 and peaked at number 38.<ref name=\"France\"/> In Finland, the single debuted and peaked at number 20.<ref name=\"Finland\"/> On the top sixty Swedish [[Sverigetopplistan]], the single debuted at number 49, peaked at number 29, and spent twenty-four weeks on that chart.<ref name=\"Sweden\"/> It was certified quadruple platinum by the [[Swedish Recording Industry Association]] (GLF), denoting sales of 80,000 copies.<ref name=\"GLF\">{{cite web |url=http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/index.html |title=Veckolista Singlar \u2013 Vecka 3, 20 januari 2012 |date= 17 January 2012 |publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]] ([[Swedish Recording Industry Association]]) |accessdate=22 January 2012|language=Swedish}}</ref> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" debuted at number 15 and peaked at number 7 on the [[ARIA Charts|Australian Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"Australia\"/> The single spent twenty-five weeks in the Australian Singles Chart top twenty.<ref name=\"Australia\"/> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" has been certified six times platinum by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA), denoting sales of 420,000 units.<ref name=\"singleAus2011\">{{cite web|url=http://www.aria.com.au/pages/httpwww.aria.com.aupagesSINGLEaccreds2012.htm|title=ARIA Charts \u2013 Accreditations \u2013 2012 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|accessdate=28 July 2012}}</ref> \"Na Na Na\" also appeared on the Australian Singles Chart of 28 November 2011 at number 84.<ref name=\"NaNaNaAUS\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/pages/chartifacts.htm |title=Chartifacts \u2013 Week Commencing: 28th November 2011 |publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association |date=28 November 2011 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63ZECkNXs?url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/pages/chartifacts.htm |archivedate=29 November 2011}}</ref> On the [[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand|New Zealand Singles Chart]], the single entered at number 16, and peaked at number 2 in its fourth and fifth weeks. The song spent eleven consecutive weeks in the chart's top ten.<ref name=\"NZchart 2\">{{cite web |url=https://charts.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=One+Direction&titel=What+Makes+You+Beautiful&cat=s |title=One Direction \u2013 What Makes You Beautiful |publisher=charts.nz |accessdate=4 January 2012}}</ref> It was certified double platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand]] (RIANZ), denoting sales of 30,000 units.<ref name=\"NZcert\">{{cite web |url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=1868 |title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart |date=5 March 2012 |publisher=Recording Industry Association of New Zealand |accessdate=3 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe single debuted on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] at number 9, while bowing at number 2 on the Canadian Hot Digital Songs Chart with 19,000 downloads sold, the biggest debut for a first time charted artist since the [[Stereos]]'s \"[[Summer Girl (Stereos song)|Summer Girl]]\" entered at number two in June 2009.<ref name=\"WMYBBillboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/one-direction-mn0002766592/awards|title=One Direction > Charts & Awards > Billboard Singles|accessdate=28 September 2012|work=AllMusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation|location=United States}}</ref> The single peaked at number 7 on the Canadian Hot 100 and has been certified quadruple platinum by [[Music Canada]], denoting sales of 320,000 copies.<ref name=\"WMYBBillboard\" />{{Certification Cite Ref|region=Canada|type=digital download|title=What Makes You Beautiful|artist=One Direction|date=27 November 2012 |accessdate=1 December 2012}} In the United States, \"What Makes You Beautiful\" became the highest [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] debut for a British act since 1998. On 1 March 2012, the single debuted on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at number 28, whilst bowing at number 12 on the [[Hot Digital Songs]] chart, selling 132,000 digital downloads in its first week.<ref name=\"Hot100\">{{cite web |author=Caufield, Keith|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/504475/one-direction-has-highest-hot-100-debut-for-new-uk-act-since-1998 |title=One Direction Has Highest Hot 100 Debut For New UK Act Since 1998 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=22 February 2012 |accessdate=13 March 2012}}</ref> On the week ending 21 April 2012, \"What Makes You Beautiful\" peaked at number 4.<ref>{{cite web|author=Caufield, Keith|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/496322/hot-100-fun-makes-digital-sales-history-in-sixth-week-at-no-1 |title=Hot 100: Fun. Makes Digital Sales History in Sixth Week at No. 1 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=11 April 2012 |accessdate=11 April 2012 }}</ref> As of 30 June 2012, the single had spent thirteen consecutive weeks in the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 top ten.<ref>{{cite news|author=Trust, Gary |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/chartbeat/482331/weekly-chart-notes-lmfao-katy-perry-fiona-apple |title=Weekly Chart Notes: LMFAO, Katy Perry, Fiona Apple |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=30 June 2012 |accessdate=9 June 2012}}</ref> The song also became a chart success on other ''Billboard'' charts, reaching the top five on the [[Mainstream Top 40]], [[Adult Top 40|Adult Pop Songs]], and [[Hot 100 Airplay (Radio Songs)|Hot 100 Airplay]] charts,<ref name=\"WMYBBillboard\" /> whilst topping the [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/chartbeat/484791/chart-highlights-carrie-underwood-crowns-country-songs-with-good-girl|title=Chart Highlights: Carrie Underwood Crowns Country Songs With 'Good Girl'|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=4 June 2012|accessdate=4 June 2012}}</ref> The track sold 3,881,000 copies in the United States in 2012, becoming the best-selling song by a boy band in digital history.<ref name=\"yahoo dec2012\">{{cite news |url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-extra-top-songs-2012-155237610.html |title=Chart Watch Extra: Top Songs of 2012 |author=Paul Grein|work=[[Yahoo! Music]]|publisher=[[Yahoo!]] |date=3 January 2013 |accessdate=5 January 2013 }}</ref> The song was certified quadruple platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) on 21 February 2013,<ref name=\"USCert\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?content_selector=gold-platinum-searchable-database|title=Searchable Database|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|date=21 February 2013|accessdate=23 March 2013}}</ref> and it has sold 4.8 million copies in the US as of June 2016.<ref name=\"USsales2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7408939/ask-billboard-one-directions-career-sales|title=Ask Billboard: One Direction's Career Sales|author=Trust, Gary|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=19 June 2016|accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" has sold over 7 million copies worldwide.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/19093915|title=One Direction hit 12 million sales in less than a year|date=2 August 2012 |work=[[BBC News]] |publisher=BBC|accessdate=2 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Singles==\n\u201cWhat Makes You Beautiful\u201d was released as the lead single along with the release of the EP. It was a no. 1 hit on the UK singles chart.\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"What Makes You Beautiful\" was directed by John Urbano. Filmed over two days in July 2011,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/music/mtvs-most-wanted/video/mtvs-most-wanted-one-direction-what-makes-you-beautiful |title=MTV's Most Wanted: What Makes You Beautiful Video |work=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[MTV Networks]] |format=video |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/one-direction/327333-one-direction-single-cher-lloyd-x-factor |title=One Direction Announce Debut Single |work=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[MTV Networks]] |date=8 August 2011 |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref> it premiered on 19 August 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.ie/music/news/a336044/one-direction-unveil-what-makes-you-beautiful-video.html |title=One Direction unveil 'What Makes You Beautiful' video |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=Hearst Magazines UK|date=19 August 2011 |accessdate=4 January 2012 |first=Lewis |last=Corner}}</ref> On each of the five days preceding the video's premiere, One Direction posted a [[Teaser campaign|teaser trailer]] of the video online. Each teaser showed footage from the video and behind the scenes, and one member of the band announcing how many days were left until the video premiere.<ref>Video teasers: \n{{YouTube|URyjCS4wMVw|1 (14 August)}}; {{YouTube|CdX6j6Yb06Y|2 (15 August)}}; {{YouTube|6zuJazE4ED4|3 (16 August)}}; {{YouTube|1SG2WZStUTQ|4 (17 August)}}; {{YouTube|Vs4WqS352ok|5 (18 August)}}; [[One Direction]]/[[Vevo]]. Retrieved 4 January 2012.</ref> The video opens with One Direction spending time on a [[Malibu, California]] beach intercut with scenes of them driving an orange [[campervan]]. During the second verse, a group of three girls joins the band at the beach; in Styles' bridge solo, he intimately sings to one girl, Madison McMullin,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Macatee|first1=Rebecca|title=Where Is the Girl From 1D's ''What Makes You Beautiful'' Video Today?|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/788822/one-direction-s-what-makes-you-beautiful-turns-5-where-is-the-girl-in-the-music-video-today|website=[[E! Online]]|publisher=NBCUniversal|accessdate=30 October 2017|date=20 August 2016}}</ref> individually. During the final choruses the band and girls are shown sitting around a fire, lighting [[sparkler]]s and taking photographs.<ref name=\"watch\"/> On video sharing website [[MUZU TV]], the video was the fourth most-watched music video of 2011 in the UK.<ref name=\"4music.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.4music.com/news/news/2480/2011s-most-watched-music-videos-revealed |title=2011\u2019s most-watched music videos revealed |work=[[4Music]] |publisher=[[Bauer Verlagsgruppe|Bauer Group]]/[[Channel Four Television Corporation]] |date=28 December 2011 |accessdate=16 April 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126103747/http://www.4music.com/news/news/2480/2011s-most-watched-music-videos-revealed |archive-date=26 January 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The video won two [[2012 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]] for [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Pop Video|Best Pop Video]] and Most Share-Worthy Video, and earned the group the award for [[MTV Video Music Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]] on 6 September 2012.<ref>{{cite news|author=Amelia Butterfly |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/19515754 |title=One Direction win three MTV Video Music Awards in LA|work=[[Newsbeat]]|publisher=BBC|date=7 September 2012|accessdate=7 September 2012}}</ref> As of November 2019, the music video has received 1.1 billion [[Vevo]] and [[YouTube]] views.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QJO3ROT-A4E |title=One Direction \u2013 What Makes You Beautiful |publisher=[[One Direction]]/[[Vevo]] |accessdate=27 July 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\n[[File:Zayn Malik and Liam Payne Today Show 2.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Malik and Payne performing \"What Makes You Beautiful\" at the [[Rockefeller Center]] on 12 March 2012]]\nOne Direction performed \"What Makes You Beautiful\" for the first time on ''[[Red or Black?]]'' on 10 September 2011.<ref name=\"One Direction Are No. 1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/number-1/ |title=One Direction Are No. 1 |date=11 September 2011 |archivedate=3 January 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/64PbzoYTT?url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/number-1/ |publisher=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]] ([[Global Radio]])}}</ref> The performance started with hosts [[Ant & Dec]] announcing that the band was supposedly running late for their appearance, and cut to a video of One Direction boarding a [[London Underground|London Tube]] carriage full of fans, as the studio version of the song began playing. Each fan on the tube was given a numbered ticket. The band and fans disembarked the tube and made their way to the television studio, where the remainder of the song was sung live. After the song, Styles caught a numbered ticket raining onstage. The number corresponded to a ticket held by a fan from the tube; the colour of the fan's shirt was the correct answer for the ''Red or Black?'' challenge.<ref name=\"One Direction Are No. 1\"/><ref>{{cite episode |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=igMf_nbglRQ |title=One Direction |season=1 |number=7 |series=Red or Black? |serieslink=Red or Black?|network=[[ITV1]] |airdate=10 September 2011 |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> The band performed \"What Makes You Beautiful\" after its B-side, \"Na Na Na\", at the [[BBC Radio 1|BBC Radio&nbsp;1]] Teen Awards on 9 October 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/15236506 |title=In pictures: Radio 1 Teen Awards at Wembley Arena|work=[[Newsbeat]] |publisher=BBC |date=10 October 2011 |archivedate=3 January 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/64PekqvoH?url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/15236506}}</ref> The band also performed the song to open telethon ''[[Children in Need 2011]]'' on 19 November 2011.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-15790669 |title=Record \u00a326m for Children in Need |date=19 November 2011 |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC|accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> After \"[[Gotta Be You (One Direction song)|Gotta Be You]]\" and \"[[One Thing (One Direction song)|One Thing]]\", One Direction performed \"What Makes You Beautiful\" at [[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]]'s ''[[Jingle Bell Ball]]'' on 4 December 2011, at [[The O2 Arena (London)|The O<sub>2</sub> Arena]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/fan-tears-jingle-bell-ball/ |title=One Direction Reduce Fans To Tears During Set At Jingle Bell Ball 2011 |date=4 December 2011 |accessdate=24 January 2012 |publisher=Capital FM (Global Radio)}}</ref> They performed a medley of \"[[She Makes Me Wanna]]\" and \"What Makes You Beautiful\" with [[JLS]] on ''The X Factor''{{'s}} [[The X Factor (UK series 8)|eighth series]] final on 10 December 2011.t{{cn|date=December 2019}} The group performed \"One Thing\" and \"What Makes You Beautiful\" on ''[[Dancing on Ice (series 7)#Week 5 (5 February)|Dancing on Ice]]'' on 5 February 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/homepage/694412/watch-again-one-directions-dancing-ice-performances-interview |title= WATCH AGAIN: ONE DIRECTION'S DANCING ON ICE PERFORMANCES & INTERVIEW|last=Lucey|first=Kate|work=[[Sugarscape.com]]|publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi M\u00e9dias]]|date=6 February 2012|accessdate=17 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn Italy, the band performed the song at the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2012|2012 Sanremo Music Festival]] on 14 February 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shineon-media.com/2012/02/20/one-direction-performs-at-the-san-remo-song-festival-video/ |title=One Direction Performs at the San Remo Song Festival (Video) |work=Shine On Media|publisher=Shine Limited |accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref> In France, they performed \"What Makes You Beautiful\" and \"One Thing\" on ''[[Le Grand Journal (Canal+)|Le Grand Journal]]'' on 22 February 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.terrafemina.com/societe/buzz/articles/11262-one-direction-revoir-le-grand-journal-en-video-streaming.html |title=One Direction : revoir le Grand Journal en vid\u00e9o streaming |work=Terrafemina |publisher=(Terrafemina Groupe M\u00e9dias)|accessdate=11 June 2012|language=French}}</ref> In the United States, One Direction performed the song along with \"[[More than This (One Direction song)|More than This]]\" and \"One Thing\" for the first time on ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|The Today Show]]'' at the [[Rockefeller Center]] on 12 March 2012. An estimated 15,000 fans descended on the plaza. Melissa Lonner, senior entertainment producer for ''The Today Show'', said: \"One Direction is relatively unknown with no hits yet. They basically exploded, and all the adults are saying, 'Who are these people, and how do they know about it?'\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/499360/one-direction-the-wanted-the-billboard-cover-story |title=One Direction & The Wanted: The Billboard Cover Story |author=Horowitz, Steven J.|work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |date=27 March 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> They also performed the song at the [[2012 Kids' Choice Awards]] on 31 March 2012.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1682190/one-direction-kids-choice-awards-performance-2012.jhtml |title=One Direction Get Celebs Dancing At Kids' Choice Awards |first=Katie |last=Byrne |publisher=[[MTV News]] ([[MTV Networks]]) |date=31 March 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> One Direction performed \"What Makes You Beautiful\" and \"One Thing\" on the NBC comedy television show ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' on 7 April 2012, and also appeared in a [[sketch comedy|comedy sketch]] with [[Sof\u00eda Vergara]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/videos/new-and-hot/one-direction-what-makes-you-beautiful-on-snl-20120408 |title='What Makes You Beautiful' on 'SNL' |work=Rolling Stone |publisher=[[Jann Wenner]]|date=8 April 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> In Australia, they performed \"One Thing\" and \"What Makes You Beautiful\" at the [[Logie Awards of 2012|54th Logie Awards]], where they also presented an award for \"Most Popular New Female Talent\" on 15 April 2012.<ref>{{cite web|author=Peel, Sarah |url=http://www.bsckids.com/2012/04/one-direction-present-perform-at-2012-logie-awards/ |title=One Direction Present & Perform At 2012 Logie Awards|work=BSC KIDS|publisher=Boomtron LLC|date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=28 June 2012}}</ref> On 12 August 2012, One Direction performed \"What Makes You Beautiful\" at the [[2012 Summer Olympics closing ceremony]] in London, which represented the handover to Rio de Janeiro as the host of the [[2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Kia Makarechi |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/08/12/one-direction-closing-ceremony-olympics_n_1770803.html |title=One Direction & Closing Ceremony: Olympics Get A Dose Of 'What Makes You Beautiful'|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|publisher=TheHuffingtonPost.com, Inc.|date=12 August 2012|accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref> It was included on the [[set list]] of the group's headlining sold-out show at [[Madison Square Garden]] on 3 December 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/473866/one-direction-headlines-sold-out-show-at-madison-square-garden|title=One Direction Headlines Sold-Out Show at Madison Square Garden|date=4 December 2012|accessdate=7 December 2012|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|author=Andrew Hampp}}</ref> One Direction performed the song on two of their major concert tours: ''[[Up All Night Tour]]'' (2011\u201312) and ''[[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]]'' (2013).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/up-all-night-uk-tour/ |title=One Direction Launch 'Up All Night' UK Tour In Wolverhampton |date=22 December 2011 |work=Capital |publisher=Global Radio|accessdate=8 April 2012|archiveurl=http://www.freezepage.com/1333940737LJKEAEHLSA?url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/up-all-night-uk-tour/ |archivedate=9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/take-me-home-world-tour-launch-london |title=One Direction Launch 'Take Me Home' World Tour With Two Sold-Out Shows In London |date=22 February 2013 |work=Capital FM |publisher=Global Radio |accessdate=23 March 2013|archiveurl=http://www.freezepage.com/1362122125ZJUWSASAOP?url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/take-me-home-world-tour-launch-london |archivedate=1 March 2013}}</ref>\nAlso this song added in ''[[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]]'' (2014) & ''[[On the Road Again Tour]]'' (2015). The second verse of the song had originally been sung by Malik. After Malik's departure, Payne took his verse.\nIn 2017, Harry performed the song on his [[Harry Styles: Live on Tour|first solo tour]].\n\n==Cover versions==\n* The song was covered for American television series [[Glee (TV series)|''Glee'']] by [[Kevin McHale (actor)|Kevin McHale]], [[Chord Overstreet]], [[Harry Shum, Jr.]], [[Samuel Larsen]], and [[Damian McGinty]] in the episode titled \"[[Prom-asaurus]]\".<ref name=\"Futterman2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/news/glee-recap-youre-insecure-dont-know-what-for-20120509|title='Glee' Recap: You're Insecure, Don't Know What For One Direction, Selena Gomez and Ke$ha soundtrack a lackluster prom episode|author=Futterman, Erica|date=9 May 2012|work=Rolling Stone |publisher=Jann Wenner|accessdate=14 May 2012}}</ref> It was first aired on 8 May 2012, and is the 19th episode of the [[Glee (season 3)|third season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvrecaps.ew.com/recap/glee-season-three-episode-19-prom/|title='Glee' recap: Dinosaurs or Bust. Rachel throws an anti-prom party and Quinn is keeping a big secret|author=Strecker, Erin|date=9 May 2012|page=1|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]] ([[Time Inc.]])|accessdate=14 May 2012}}</ref> Their characters [[Artie Abrams]] (McHale), [[Sam Evans]] (Overstreet), [[Mike Chang]] (Shum), [[Joe Hart (Glee)|Joe Hart]] (Larsen), and [[Rory Flanagan]] (McGinty), covered the song in the episode, performing a choreographed dance routine to it.<ref name=\"Maloy\">{{cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/489096/glee-covers-one-directions-what-makes-you-beautiful-watch |title='Glee' Covers One Direction's 'What Makes You Beautiful': Watch|author=Maloy, Sarah |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=5 May 2012 |accessdate=24 July 2012}}</ref> Sarah Maloy of ''Billboard'' acknowledged, \"Screaming girls and choreographed boy band moves are, of course, in no short supply.\"<ref name=\"Maloy\"/> Maloy described ''Glee''{{'}}s version as \"barely changing the sound or style of the original version.\"<ref name=\"Maloy\"/> Erica Futterman of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' wrote, \"While One Direction's original manages to pack a pop punch, ''Glee''{{'}}s take kind of hits the mark. (Literally. The ''Glee'' boys prance across the stage in the same path as the U.K. heartthrobs.)\" Futterman concluded that it was the fourth best performance of that episode.<ref name=\"Futterman2\"/> ''Glee''{{'s}} cover was released for digital download through the [[iTunes Store]] on 8 May 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/what-makes-you-beautiful-glee/id523218909?i=523218912&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=What Makes You Beautiful (Glee Cast Version)|publisher=[[iTunes]] ([[Apple Inc]])|accessdate=14 May 2012}}</ref> It charted at numbers 93 and 163 on the Canadian Hot 100 and UK Singles Chart, respectively.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/120519cluk.txt | title=UK Singles Chart: CLUK Update (19.05.2012 \u2013 week 19) | accessdate=20 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=glee|chart=Billboard Canadian Hot 100}}&sort=date |title=Glee Album & Song Chart History: Billboard Canadian Hot 100 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=10 May 2012}}</ref>\n* In July 2012, [[the Piano Guys]] uploaded on YouTube an instrumental piano version of the song, which went [[viral phenomenon|viral]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Halperin|first=Shirley|title=One Direction's 'What Makes You Beautiful' Gets Plucky Makeover by The Piano Guys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/one-direction-what-makes-you-beautiful-piano-guys-351979|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time Inc]]|accessdate=17 November 2012|date=19 July 2012}}</ref>\n* Chinese [[Mandopop]] band [[TFBoys]] covered in Chinese version \u300a\u300a\u9752\u86d9\u4e5f\u4f1a\u53d8\u738b\u5b50\u300b\u300b(The frog also can become Prince).\n\n==Track listing==\n;Digital download and CD single<ref name=\"AUSiTunes\"/> \n#\"What Makes You Beautiful\" \u2013 3:24\n#\"[[Na Na Na (One Direction song)|Na Na Na]]\" \u2013 3:10\n\n==Credits and personnel==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;\"What Makes You Beautiful\"\n*[[Tom Coyne (music engineer)|Tom Coyne]] \u2013 [[audio mastering|mastering]]\n*[[Carl Falk]] \u2013 writing, production, [[Programming (music)|programming]], [[Musical instrument|instruments]], guitar\n*Serban Ghenea \u2013 [[audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]]\n*John Hanes \u2013 [[mix engineer]]ing\n*[[Savan Kotecha]] \u2013 writing\n*Phil Seaford \u2013 mix engineering assistance\n*[[Rami Yacoub]] \u2013 writing, production, programming, instruments, bass\n{{col-2}}\n;\"Na Na Na\"\n*Dick Beetham \u2013 [[audio mastering|mastering]]\n*Iain James \u2013 [[songwriter|writing]]\n*[[Savan Kotecha]] \u2013 writing\n*Matt Lawrence \u2013 [[audio engineering|engineering]]\n*Greg Marriot \u2013 engineering assistance\n*James Murray \u2013 writing\n*[[Matt Squire]] \u2013 writing, production, backing vocals, [[audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]]\n*Mustapha Omer \u2013 writing<ref name=\"credits\">{{cite AV media notes |title=What Make You Beautiful |others=[[One Direction]] |type=CD liner |location=UK |publisher=[[Syco Music]] ([[Sony Music Entertainment]])}}</ref>\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2011\u201312)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Australia|7|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful|refname=\"Australia\"}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Austria|28|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Flanders|8|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful|refname=\"Flanders\"}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Wallonia|19|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful|refname=\"Wallonia\"}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Brazil ([[Billboard Brasil Hot 100|''Billboard'' Brasil Hot 100]])<ref name=\"Billboard Brasil 1-13\">{{Cite journal |last= |first= |authorlink= |author2= |date=July 2012|title=Billboard Brasil Hot 100 Airplay |journal=[[Billboard Brasil]] |issue=32 |pages=84\u201389 |id= |url= |accessdate= |editor=BPP}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|24\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Brazil [[Billboard Brasil|Hot Pop Songs]]<ref name=\"Billboard Brasil 1-13\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Billboardcanadianhot100|7|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful|artistid={{Billboard ID|One Direction}}}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Czech Republic|13|year=2012|week=19}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{Singlechart|Denmark|26|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Finland|20|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful|accessdate=13 January 2012|refname=\"Finland\"}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|France|39|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful|accessdate=13 January 2012|refname=\"France\"}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Germany|40|artist=One Direction|song=What Makes You Beautiful}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Ireland|1|year=2011|week=37|accessdate=16 September 2011|refname=\"Ireland\"}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Italy ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/notes/sony-music-italy/le-classifiche-della-settimana/10150708181765786|title=Classifica italian FIMI del 2 Marcho 2012|publisher=[[Federazion